ApplyXPathSemanticAction, BackOffFromSite, CreateAndVisualizeImgSurrogateSemanticAction, CreateAndVisualizeTextSurrogateSemanticAction, CreateContainerSemanticAction, CreateSearchSemanticAction, CreateSemanticAnchorSemanticAction, DownloadLaterSemanticAction, DownloadNowSemanticAction, EvaluateRankWeight, GeneralSemanticAction, GetFieldSemanticAction, NestedSemanticAction, SetMetadataSemanticAction, SetterSemanticAction, TrySyncNestedMetadata
public abstract class SemanticAction
extends ecologylab.xml.ElementState

This is the abstract class which defines the semantic action. All the semantic actions must extend it. To add a new semantic action following steps needed to be taken. 1) Create a class for that semantic action which extends SemanticAction class. 2) Write all the custom code for that semantic action in this new class file. [Example see ForEachSemanticAction.java orIfSemanticAction which implements for_each semantic action.] 3) Modify the handleSemanticAction method of SemanticActionHandle.java to add case for new semantic action. 4) Add a new method in SemanticActionHandler.java to handle this action. Mostly this method should be abstract unless the action is a flow control action like FOR LOOP. 5) For code clarity and readability define a constant for the new action name in SemanticActionStandardMethods.java

Author:
amathur
